Rühl
</taxonomicName>
, [1893],
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[544,1436,1794,1819]" pageId="9" pageNumber="90" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1362,1963]" box="[544,1436,1794,1819]" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">
TL: 
<collectingCountry box="[592,724,1795,1819]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
, Alai Mts (southern slope), Daroot-Korgon, 
<quantity box="[1221,1306,1795,1819]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="9" pageNumber="90" unit="m" value="2700.0">2700 m</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[1320,1422,1794,1819]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–5" captionStartId="9.[151,264,689,712]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,301,666]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[150,1436,301,669]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 3–5. The neotype of Melitaea arduinna heynei Rühl, [1893], 3: upperside; 4: underside; 5: labels. (Scale bar = 10 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3713998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3713998/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">Figs 3, 4</figureCitation>
);
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="92" pageId="9" pageNumber="90" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1362,1963]" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">
this form is small (
<typeStatus box="[406,511,1830,1855]" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">lectotype</typeStatus>
wing span only 
<quantity box="[694,776,1831,1855]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="9" pageNumber="90" unit="mm" value="34.0">34 mm</quantity>
), this feature was probably the main reason for confusing it with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Russell &amp; Lukhtanov" authorityYear="2018" box="[256,361,1867,1890]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinxia">
<emphasis box="[256,361,1867,1890]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">M. cinxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (Larger forms such as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1886" box="[627,899,1866,1890]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="arduinna" subSpecies="evanescens">
<emphasis box="[627,899,1866,1890]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">M. arduinna evanescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[954,1155,1866,1890]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">M. a. rhodopensis</emphasis>
cannot be confused with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Russell &amp; Lukhtanov" authorityYear="2018" box="[199,305,1903,1926]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinxia">
<emphasis box="[199,305,1903,1926]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">M. cinxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Ground colour similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="arduinna" box="[619,868,1902,1926]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="arduinna" subSpecies="arduinna">
<emphasis box="[619,868,1902,1926]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">M. arduinna arduinna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but black markings reduced in the postdiscal area (see also 
<figureCitation box="[303,370,1938,1963]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,831,853]" captionTargetBox="[165,1436,199,810]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[150,1436,193,810]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Melitaea cinxia, the varieties obscurior, clarissa &amp; heynei and M. arduinna, the varieties rhodopensis &amp; evanescens, figured by Seitz, 1908-1910: Plate 65, rows e (part), f and g (part)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3713996" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3713996/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), melanic females as yet unknown.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714000" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3714000" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714000/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="91" startId="10.[151,264,1852,1875]" targetBox="[151,1436,230,1798]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1852,2028]" pageId="10" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,327,1852,1875]" pageId="10" pageNumber="91">FIGURES 6–14.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Russell &amp; Lukhtanov" authorityYear="2018" box="[332,521,1852,1874]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arduinna">
<emphasis box="[332,521,1852,1874]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicName box="[332,422,1852,1874]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Melitaea</taxonomicName>
arduinna
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Russell &amp; Lukhtanov" authorityYear="2018" box="[569,665,1854,1875]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinxia">
<emphasis box="[569,665,1854,1875]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="91">M. cinxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Scale bar = 10 mm). 6-8: 
<taxonomicName authority="arduinna" box="[938,1161,1852,1875]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="arduinna" subSpecies="arduinna">
<emphasis box="[938,1161,1852,1875]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="91">M. arduinna arduinna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, Russia, Orenburg Region, Krasnoznamenka, 230 m, 30 May 2011, P. Russell leg. (6: male, upperside; 7: male, underside; 8: melanic female, upperside). 9-10: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Russell &amp; Lukhtanov" authorityYear="2018" box="[213,312,1915,1936]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinxia">
<emphasis box="[213,312,1915,1936]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="91">M. cinxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male, Russia, Orenburg Region, Krasnoznamenka, 230 m, 30 May 2011, P. Russell leg. (9: upperside; 10: underside). 11-12: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1886" box="[348,599,1944,1967]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="arduinna" subSpecies="evanescens">
<emphasis box="[348,599,1944,1967]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="91">M. arduinna evanescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male, Tajikistan, Peter the Great Mts, Ganishou, 1900 m, 30 June 2017, V. A. Lukhtanov leg. (11: upperside; 12: underside). 13-14: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freyer" authorityYear="1836" box="[706,962,1975,1997]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="arduinna" subSpecies="rhodopensis">
<emphasis box="[706,962,1975,1997]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="91">M. arduinna rhodopensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male, reared ex larvae, Serbia, Stara Planina, South of Kalna, emerged 12 June 2011, P. Russell leg. (13: upperside; 14: underside).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,392]" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ruhl" authorityYear="1893" box="[199,418,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="arduinna" subSpecies="heynei">
<emphasis box="[199,418,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">M. arduinna heynei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be a distinct subspecies. It differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1886" box="[986,1258,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="arduinna" subSpecies="evanescens">
<emphasis box="[986,1258,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">M. arduinna evanescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which inhabits nearby regions in 
<collectingCountry box="[362,490,189,213]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[551,664,188,213]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
, not only by small size, but also by the ground colour and pattern design of the hind-wing underside, which is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="arduinna" box="[868,1119,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="arduinna" subSpecies="arduinna">
<emphasis box="[868,1119,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">M. arduinna arduinna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The phenotypic difference between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ruhl" authorityYear="1893" box="[254,480,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="arduinna" subSpecies="heynei">
<emphasis box="[254,480,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">M. arduinna heynei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1886" box="[541,820,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="arduinna" subSpecies="evanescens">
<emphasis box="[541,820,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">M. arduinna evanescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be comparable to that existing between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1886" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="arduinna" subSpecies="evanescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">M. arduinna evanescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Sheljuzhko, 1914" authorityName="Sheljuzhko" authorityYear="1914" box="[446,774,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="avinovi">
<emphasis box="[446,568,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">M. avinovi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sheljuzhko, L." box="[576,774,295,320]" pageId="11" pageNumber="92" pagination="18 - 22" refId="ref10895" refString="Sheljuzhko, L. (1914) Neue Rhopaloceren vom Pamir. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift Iris, 28 (1), 18 - 22" type="journal article" year="1914">Sheljuzhko, 1914</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see Plate LXXIV, figs 
<quantity box="[1053,1140,295,320]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.032" metricValueMax="3.81" metricValueMin="0.254" pageId="11" pageNumber="92" unit="in" value="8.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="1.0">1–15 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Tshikolovets, V. V." box="[1149,1367,295,320]" pageId="11" pageNumber="92" pagination="1 - 499" refId="ref11430" refString="Tshikolovets, V. V. (2003) The butterflies of Tajikistan. The Butterflies of Palaearctic Asia, 4, 1 - 499, 77 colour pls." type="journal article" year="2003">Tshikolovets, 2003</bibRefCitation>
: 327– 328). Further, more detailed morphological, molecular and chromosomal studies (e.g. as in 
<bibRefCitation author="Lukhtanov, V. A." box="[1198,1386,332,357]" pageId="11" pageNumber="92" pagination="325 - 357" refId="ref10101" refString="Lukhtanov, V. A. (2017) A new species of Melitaea from Israel, with notes on taxonomy, cytogenetics, phylogeography and interspecific hybridization in the Melitaea persea complex (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae). Comparative Cytogenetics, 11 (2), 325 - 357. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / CompCytogen. v 11 i 2.12370" type="journal article" year="2017">Lukhtanov 2017</bibRefCitation>
) are required to clarify the status (species or subspecies) of 
<emphasis box="[766,992,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ruhl" authorityYear="1893" box="[766,989,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="arduinna" subSpecies="heynei">M. arduinna heynei</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
